    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-06-24T21:17:21+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-24T21:17:21+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-24T11:47:21Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-24T11:47:21Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system is located south of SA and is forecast to be centred over Tasmania on Thursday. The high will continue to extend a ridge over SA through to Saturday then a low pressure trough is expected to reach far western areas of the state on Sunday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW013" description="North West Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-06-24T21:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-25T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-24T11:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-24T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Light winds.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-06-25T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-26T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-24T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-25T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Medium chance of showers east of Coober Pedy, near zero chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm south of Coober Pedy in the afternoon and evening. Light winds becoming east to northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h in the morning then tending east to southeasterly in the early afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 4 and 8 with daytime temperatures reaching around 16.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 11:10am to 1:50pm, UV Index predicted to reach 3 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-06-26T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-27T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-25T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-26T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Sunny. The chance of morning fog south of Coober Pedy. Areas of morning frost north of Marla. Light winds becoming northeast to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h in the middle of the day. Overnight temperatures falling to around 5 with daytime temperatures reaching around 17.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-06-27T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-28T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-26T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-27T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower in the far west in the afternoon and evening. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds east to northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h tending north to northeasterly 15 to 25 km/h during the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to around 6 with daytime temperatures reaching between 17 and 20.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-06-28T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-29T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-27T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-28T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers in the far west, medium chance elsewhere. Winds north to northeasterly 20 to 30 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 7 and 10 with daytime temperatures reaching between 18 and 22.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
